Former Vice Predident Kalonzo Musyoka has lost his father. Peter Musyoka Mairu passed away on Sunday. Details of his death remains scanty. The Wiper Party leader and Nasa co-principal lost his mother in 2014. Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi has condoled with  the family. "My thoughts and prayers are with you and your entire family as you walk this difficult path,” Musalia tweeted. Bungoma Senator Moses Wetang'ula also eulogised Mairu 'for his iconic advise and relentless efforts on his quest to have a just society'. "His bravery, steadfastness, and personal sacrifice to see this country attain greater heights will forever be etched onto the minds of Kenyans who cherish democracy and cohesion," Wetang'ula said. Kisii governor James Ongwae said: "We stand with you (Kalonzo) at this time of mourning." Click here for the latest political news